snippet: Stealing a page from neighboring Egypt, a senior army officer in Libya announced a military takeover. But no one seemed to be taking him seriously.
abstract: Senior Libyan army officer announces a military takeover of the country, only to have the supposed coup derided by Prime Min Ali Zeidan; announcement is the latest evidence of the long shadow cast across the region by the military takeover in Egypt, but failure of coup attempt to get off the ground demonstrates limits of Egyptian example.
lead_paragraph: Stealing a page from neighboring Egypt, a senior army officer in Libya announced a military takeover. But no one seemed to be taking him seriously.

headline.main: In Libya, a Coup. Or Perhaps Not.
headline.print_headline: Libyan Coup Is Declared, Then Derided
